A security officer is in a critical condition following the hijacking of a truck on Atlas Road in Kempton Park on Tuesday. Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said reports from the scene indicated that the officer was escorting a truck transporting goods when he was shot by unknown men, Kempton Express reported. The exact detail as to what happened will form part of a police investigation. The man was stabilised on scene by Netcare 911 paramedics, and then intubated. The Netcare2 helicopter was dispatched to the scene to airlift the critically wounded officer to a level 1 trauma facility in Johannesburg for further medical care, Mathe said. &#8211; Caxton News Service